I've made a LOT of chili recipes (the official state dish of Texas!)and my fiance is usually strongly against putting beans in any chili, but even he absolutely LOVED this one with black beans and chicken! It's such a great variation on traditional chili con carne, it's unique and just superbly delicious. The puree of chiles and cashews was amazing in this recipe. I used a few more chiles than called for just because we like it extra spicy, and I always run the pureed chiles through a food mill or sieve first to remove unblended skin and seeds, then I put that back in the blender to puree with the cashews and broth. Can't wait to make this again, it's easy and fun to make and absolutely outstanding.

Rating: 4
I made this again for my school's chili cookoff and won 1st prize. For all you saying it's a hard, time consuming recipe, here are some time savers I use. Use canned chipotles in adobo and dump them into the blender with the broth and cashews. No cooking. Buy roasted chicken from the store and just debone it, throw the meat in after the spices. It is just throwing things in and letting them cook after that. My family loves this recipe, even my picky kids. Nice on a crisp fall day!

