I made this for a chili cook-off & won 3rd place. I am fairly competitive, so 3rd isn't great in my opinion, but I had some stiff competition. I made a double-batch & followed the recipe with a few exceptions. 1. I used a 7oz can of chipotles in adobo sauce as well as a small can of fire-roasted green chilis in the puree. 2. I substituted beer for half of the chicken stock volume. 3. I skinned my bone-in chicken breasts/thighs before cooking them. 4. I used 1 can of white beans & 1 can of black beans rather than kidney for color variation. 5. I did not add cashew pieces at the end - all the cashews went into the puree. I loved this chili! It was pretty labor-intensive so when I make it again, I will make at least a quadruple batch.

