I'd been looking for a different chili recipe than my usual, and thought this sounded intriguing. It was really delicious. For ease, I substituted 1 chipotle chili from a can for the ancho in the puree with great results. Since my husband and I are "spice-wimps", I would cut down the chipotle amount by half next time, but that's just our taste. I used skinless, boneless chicken thigh cutlets and substituted black beans for the kidney beans. The only ingredient I did not use was the 1/2 cup of cashews at the end -- by the time the recipe called for them to be added, I felt the chili didn't need them due to its consistency. I added about 3/4 cup of additional chicken broth at the end because the chili was getting too thick, and that made the consistency perfect. Added a dollop of sour cream and chopped fresh cilantro to each serving and served with cornbread on the side.Because I used boneless chicken, it was super fast beginning to end -- a great last minute meal for after work on a weekday or even a weekend football game. Definitely my new go-to chili recipe for awhile!

