After making this recipe I was actually compelled to write my first comment. I made this exactly as written (substituting a chipotle chili for the ancho), even using measuring spoons for the spices and weighing the chicken. I used roasted/salted cashews, and rinsed them to remove some salt before pureeing. I added more cashews a few minutes before serving, lightly chopping so they weren't whole, but they were still nice big chunks. The only flaw with this recipe is that there were no leftovers. The flavors are rich and complex, and yet worked so nicely together. The chicken cooked in the puree is saturated with flavor. So many recipes are 'a nice starting point' as long as the cook uses some creativity to add some spunk. But this recipe is the whole package. Sure, you can add some spunk if it suits you, but this recipe can respectably stand on its own. There it is. My first review.

