Rating: 4
This was really good, but not quite "wow." I think my modifications made a difference. I used only boneless chicken breasts (and cut the amount back by about 25%, which was a good idea), and I think this made the dish less rich & flavorful. I'll use the darker & bone-in meat next time (but I'm not sure I could bring myself to let the skin cook along with everything else--I have a grease phobia!). I also couldn't find ancho chilis but did find fresh poblano...so I dried them in the oven, and they may have lost some flavor through my inexpert methods. I also think I might use crushed tomatoes next time instead of the diced for more of an intense tomato flavor disbursed throughout the dish. But it was good anyway; I just wanted more of an intensity of flavor.

